allenge outdated notions about gender, race, and aboriginality within the penal system, instead of addressing concerns around diversity, these measures end up contributing to further exclusion and discrimination within the system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofxCanada. 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzCanada. 0aDiscrimination in criminal justice administrationxCanada. 0aDiscrimination in criminal justice administrationzCanada. 0aParolexCanada. 0aParolezCanada. 0aParoleesxCanada. 0aParoleeszCanada. 0aWomen paroleesxCanada. 0aWomen paroleeszCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Penology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311141795040uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483195640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774831956423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774831956/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-141795-0  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles